description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit Health Visitors to join our Bank Register to work within the Health Visiting Service in Powys. The post-holders will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;work within Health Visiting teams and have responsibility for caseload management and the delivery of the Healthy Child Wales programme.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;work effectively to promote the health and well-being of children and their families,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ensure a high quality service to families, individuals and groups in the community for the promotion of their physical, social and psychological wellbeing.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Applicants should be a registered nurse with a registered health visitor qualification. Good written and verbal communication skills, evidence of multi-agency working and child protection experience are essential. The applicants must also be able to demonstrate evidence of on-going professional development. Knowledge of the current health agenda relating to children, families and health visiting is a necessity. The post-holders must be able to travel to undertake the duties of the post at various locations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
